mutant: m026_commit_rev_altered
target: internal/ingest/live/events.go
failure-mode: |
  In convertVerifiedOps (the MAIN live #commit path), the archived Rev is
  ALTERED rather than dropped (commit.Rev + "x"). Models a corruption /
  mis-copy that produces a wrong-but-non-empty rev. Unlike m014/m018 (which
  empty the rev and trip CheckInvariants' monotonicity), a wrong non-empty
  rev still increases monotonically, so the per-DID rev-regression invariant
  does NOT fire — only an exact rev-field comparison catches it.
expected-detection: |
  Killed by the EVENT-LOG tier: assertFirehoseEventLogMatches compares
  normalized rows including the rev field, so the altered rev surfaces as
  "event mismatch at index N ... fields: rev". Default tier.

  This mutant is the #104 proof that rev correctness is owned by the
  event-log tier, not the final-state tier. The final-state Compare
  deliberately does NOT compare rev (ground truth cannot populate a correct
  per-record rev, and a #sync resync collapses records to the sync rev), so
  this mutant is INVISIBLE to Compare — verified: it is caught only by the
  event-log comparison, with equal payload and a converged final state.
expected-tier: default
tiers: default,stress

diff --git a/internal/ingest/live/events.go b/internal/ingest/live/events.go
--- a/internal/ingest/live/events.go
+++ b/internal/ingest/live/events.go
@@ -156 +156 @@ func convertVerifiedOps(evt streaming.Event, indexedAt int64) ([]segment.Event,
-			Rev:                 commit.Rev,
+			Rev:                 commit.Rev + "x",
